<p>I am trying to create a simple proxy using rewrite.<br> the following code will create an error: HTTP Error 404.4 - Not Found  </p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt; &lt;configuration&gt;   &lt;system.webServer&gt;     &lt;rewrite&gt;       &lt;rules&gt;         &lt;rule name="Rewrite ASP" stopProcessing="true"&gt;           &lt;match url=".*" /&gt;           &lt;action type="Rewrite" url="http://orig:7071" /&gt;         &lt;/rule&gt;       &lt;/rules&gt;     &lt;/rewrite&gt;   &lt;/system.webServer&gt; &lt;/configuration&gt; </code></pre>  <p>If I change to <code>&lt;action type="Rewrite" url="http://orig:7071" /&gt;</code> it will redirect... but I need rewrite.</p>  <p>I dont know if this leads us anywhere, the following code will generate the following error:<br> HTTP Error 500.50 - URL Rewrite Module Error.<br> The expression "<a href="http://orig:7071/" rel="nofollow">http://orig:7071/</a>{R:1}" cannot be expanded.  </p>  <pre><code>&lt;action type="Rewrite" url="http://orig:7071/{R:1}" /&gt; </code></pre>